<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-OFFENSE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SYDOR, VERBEEK GIVE STARS A SPARK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAULA CABALLERO 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Remember when Stars coach Ken Hitchcock was thinking of
moving defenseman Darryl Sydor to forward?
</P>
<P>
   Hitchcock was going to pair Sydor with Mike Modano and Jere
Lehtinen on the Stars' top line.
</P>
<P>
   He didn't. And he didn't have to. Sydor scored off a Modano pass
for the game-winning goal.
</P>
<P>
   Remember little scrapper Pat Verbeek? Hitchcock moved him to
Modano's line last night. He scored on an odd-man rush with Richard
Matvichuk, on a play set up by _ surprise _ Modano.
</P>
<P>
   Modano needed finishers. Last night, he found them.
</P>
<P>
   Unlikely heroes? Maybe. Neither had a point in this series.
</P>
<P>
   ``I guess I haven't really done much offensively,'' Sydor said.
</P>
<P>
   But Sydor and Verbeek are hardly incapable. Sydor has two goals
and 11 points in the playoffs, and Verbeek has two goals and six
points.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps these two were simply due.
</P>
<P>
   And elated to make a difference on the scoreboard.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tonight, to play in this game in front of our fans with the
intensity both teams throw out on the ice, it's great to be an
athlete,'' Verbeek said. ``It's great to be a hockey player and I'm
really enjoying myself.''
</P>
<P>
   Now don't think Mike Modano's input last night has been
overlooked. He knew he had to step up. But sometimes when great
players step up, they press, trying to score.
</P>
<P>
   Modano shined by lifting those around him, by making them the
heroes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told him \RHitchcock\S I was going to be a player involved
in every aspect of the game,'' Modano said.
</P>
<P>
   The result of the multihero night was a multigoal victory in a
big-time game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our team all year has been a team where somebody different
steps up, we don't rely on one guy,'' Sydor said. ``We all know
what's at the end of the tunnel. We all have to sacrifice.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who knows who the next hero will be?''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
