<HEADER>
A0303 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ALLSTATE-FRAUD-LADN     06-18 0405
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALLSTATE-FRAUD-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ALLSTATE SUING PROVIDERS TO GET $16 MILLION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY GREGORY J. WILCOX  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Continuing its battle against what it says is
medical billing fraud, Allstate Insurance Co. on Thursday sued 21
California health care providers, including nine clinics in the Los
Angeles area, for $16 million.
</P>
<P>
   Defendants in the Los Angeles area include the Van Nuys Family
Health Center at 14402 Haynes St. and its owner, chiropractor
Behrouz Meshkinfam.
</P>
<P>
   The Northbrook, Ill., insurer claims that the doctors,
chiropractors and medical facilities it is targeting submitted
excessive bills for treatments provided.
</P>
<P>
   ``A guy comes in with a little neck pain and they were treating
it like it was a life-threatening condition,'' said Los Angeles
attorney Dennis B. Kass, who is representing Allstate in the local
actions.
</P>
<P>
   ``In fact they were doing nothing. We have 307 sets of medical
records sitting before us and they are all the same,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Meshkinfam was the only person named in the suits that could be
reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have any information about that,'' he said of Allstate
allegations.
</P>
<P>
   Other individuals named in the suit are Dr. Hisham Muhyeldin,
Dr. Feras Haddad and chiropractors Noland Coons, Elyas Khury and
Jacqueline Ganjeh. Their hometowns were not available.
</P>
<P>
   The other medical facilities are Tri-Star Family Health Center,
10640 E. Valley Blvd. in El Monte owned by Muhyeldin; Wilshire
Tri-Star Medical Clinic at 2500 Wilshire Blvd., owned by Haddad;
Carson Community Medical Clinic, 675 E. University Drive and the
Carson Medical Clinic at the same address, both owned by Haddad;
Wilshire Rampart Health Center, owned by Muhyeldin; Value Care
Medical Clinic at 2412 S. Azusa Ave. in West Covina, owned by
Muhyeldin; Anaheim Walk In Medical Clinic at 842 S. Brookhurst in
Anaheim, owned by Muhyeldin; and El Monte Valley Health Center at
10640 E. Valley Blvd., owned by Haddad.
</P>
<P>
   Allstate has taken an aggressive stance against medical
insurance fraud. Last year, the company filed a $107 million
lawsuit in California against a ring that Allstate alleges has been
bilking insurers since at least 1992. The case is pending.
</P>
<P>
   Kass said that the company's first step following Thursday's
filing will be trying to settle the cases out of court.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
