<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Germany returned to military action in Kosovo as
a well-established democratic nation in the company of other
democratic nations fighting to end a policy of murderous ethnic
abuse. Imagine that. Sometimes you win one. Really win one. (Tom
Teepen is national correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED
THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ On Tuesday, my doctor wrote me a prescription
for Rezulin, a drug used to treat type-2 diabetes. I am among an
estimated 15 million Americans with the disease. On Wednesday, the
Food and Drug Administration issued a report saying that there is
``further evidence of serious and sometimes fatal liver injury in
patients treated with Rezulin.'' (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist
for Cox News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ Several years ago, as personal
computing became more widely popular, I told a friend named Sandy
Greenberg about a voice recognition program that I'd been testing.
He leaped at the chance to use it too. (Andy Glass is a columnist
for Cox News Service in the Washington bureau.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
