<HEADLINE>
PICTURE THIS: YOUR DOG A STAR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I have a dog that is unusual-looking _ everyone says he
should be on a calendar. Where does a person get in touch with a
dog agent?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.K., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: One Fort Worth-Dallas company that is looking for dogs, birds
and more-exotic creatures is Animal Trackers at Box 4313, Dallas
75208.
</P>
<P>
   Company owner David Parr said you should send four 35mm
photographs of your animal and a sheet of paper that lists your
name, address, phone number and the commands your dog knows.
</P>
<P>
   ```Sit' is 90 percent of photo work, and `come' is 50 percent of
all commercial work,'' Parr said. He isn't looking for any cats,
regardless of talent. ``They are just so finicky, and there's so
much odd noise _ building sets and other things _ that it scares
them.''
</P>
<P>
   In other areas, the best place to find an animal agent is
through a local or state film commission, said Barbara O'Brien, who
calls herself ``top dog'' of the Animal Connection agency in
Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   O'Brien will look at snapshots of animals sent to Animal
Connection, 233 W. Poplar St. W., South St. Paul, MN 55075 _
``especially if they have something really unusual,'' she said. Put
your name, address and phone number on the back of each picture you
send.
</P>
<P>
   Animal Connection has a Web site at www.animal-connection.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: A Tony Danza commercial for a phone company features someone
who looks a lot like him. Is it his son?
</P>
<P>
   _ C.C., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Danza appears in an MCI commercial with his son, Marc, a
27-year-old venue planner for ESPN's X Games.
</P>
<P>
   Danza was 19 when his son was born. People magazine included the
pair in the father-and-son category of its 1998 ``Sexiest Man
Alive'' issue.
</P>
<P>
   ``We sort of grew up together, so we're pretty friendly,'' Tony
Danza told the magazine. Each served as best man at the other's
wedding. Tony Danza also has daughters ages 5 and 11.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
