seed and you get a handful of crops,'' a local saying goes. With a
per capita income of less than $100 a year, this is one of the
poorest regions in China. But recently this barren, brown wasteland
has yielded a lucrative new crop that stands to repay the
generations of suffering: a cache of nearly intact
15-million-year-old fossils, which the villagers plan to sell. By
