<P>
   WICCANS _ The witches of Fort Hood, under fire from the
religious right, hold a nighttime ceremony in support of religious
tolerance. The witches are going beyond Fort Hood: A national pagan
prayer circle for religious tolerance sponored by the Military
Pagan Network is scheduled for June 28 at the Jefferson Memorial in
Washington, D.C. (Perkes, Austin American-Statesman).
