<P>
   (NYT23) DINGJIAERGOU, China -- June 18, 1999 -- CHINA-FOSSILS,
6-18 -- Ding Yaohong, a farmer, sits next to the fossil of a
ancient spade-toothed elephant. For years, farmers in the region
have struggled to coax wheat and corn from their land. However a
lucrative new crop stands to repay the generations of suffering: a
cache of nearly intact 15 million-year-old fossils, which the
villagers plan to sell. (Elisabeth Rosenthal/New York Times Photo)
LITE
