<SLUG> BC-BKN-FINALS-WAGERS19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    All bets are on in interstate NBA rivalry
 &HT;    By Christian Davenport
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ U.S. Sen. Phil Gramm fired the first salvo from
his Washington office.
</P>
<P>
   ``Eat our dust, city boy,'' he said to his New York counterpart,
Sen. Charles Schumer. ``And, hey, what the heck is a Knick
anyhow?''
</P>
<P>
   Schumer fired back as quickly as a Texas outlaw: ``Even Davy
Crockett couldn't help the Spurs pull this one off,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Since the beginning of the National Basketball Association
championship series, which pits the New York Knicks against the San
Antonio Spurs, harsh words and wagers have been flying between the
Empire State and the Lone Star State.
</P>
<P>
   If the Spurs win, Democrat Schumer has vowed to send Republican
Gramm smoked salmon, bagels and cannolis from New York.
</P>
<P>
   ``What the heck is a cannoli?'' Gramm said. ``I guess I'll be
finding out soon.''
</P>
<P>
   If the Knicks win, Gramm has to send Schumer a case of wine from
Lubbock's Llano Estacado Winery and Mars candies from Waco.
</P>
<P>
   They are not the only state leaders laying it on the line.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio Mayor Howard Peak wagered a case of Lone Star beer,
tamales and chips and salsa against New York Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani's Brooklyn Beer, Nathan's hot dogs and cheesecake from
Junior's restaurant in Brooklyn.
</P>
<P>
   They added a touch of humiliation to whoever loses the bet: The
loser has to wear the opponent's baseball cap in public.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking forward to seeing him wear that hat,'' Peak said.
</P>
<P>
   Texas Gov. George W. Bush is betting New York Gov. George Pataki
a pair of cowboy boots _ with spurs, of course. Pataki said he'll
send Bush sandwiches from Ben's Best Deli and a dozen bagels.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-18-99 2150EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
