<SLUG> BC-BULLOCK-REACT19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Friends, colleagues react to Bullock's death
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   `There are no words big enough to capture Bob Bullock. Unique
seems an understatement. Even legend or giant are not big enough.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Gov. George W. Bush
</P>
<P>
   `Bob Bullock was a man always in search of problems to be
solved. Through his creativity, he could always find a solution,
and through the force of his personality, he turned his ideas into
reality.'
</P>
<P>
   _ House Speaker Pete Laney
</P>
<P>
   `Whatever I have accomplished in the Texas Senate is owed to Bob
Bullock. When asked in the future about the great men in my life,
Bob Bullock is one of the ones who stands above the rest.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Sen. David Sibley, R-Waco
</P>
<P>
   `Bob Bullock loved Texas with every fiber of his iron fist and
kind heart. I'm glad I knew him. He truly broke the mold, and there
will never be another Texas leader like him.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Lt. Gov. Rick Perry
</P>
<P>
   `Bob Bullock loved state government _ first, last and always. He
literally gave everything he had to his public service, and no
person could be asked to do more.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Former Gov. Ann Richards
</P>
<P>
   `The story of Bob Bullock's career is the story of the
modernization of state government in Texas. But for all the
computers he bought and for all the efficiencies he achieved, Bob
Bullock never lost sight of old Texas values: independence,
dignity, loyalty, the search for truth and devotion to God and
country.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Joe Gunn, Texas AFL-CIO president
</P>
<P>
   `Among Texas Democrats, depending on the situation, Bob Bullock
was cussed or discussed, loved or loathed, but he was always
respected for his absolute dedication to our great state.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Molly Beth Malcolm, Texas Democratic Party chairwoman
</P>
<P>
   `Bob Bullock's love and passion for the state of Texas was
appreciated, admired and will be sorely missed.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Susan Weddington, Texas Republican Party chairwoman
</P>
<P>
   `(Sam) Houston, (Stephen F.) Austin, (Lyndon B.) Johnson and
(Sam) Rayburn better make room at the table for Bullock.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Railroad Commissioner Tony Garza
</P>
<P>
   `Bob Bullock doesn't remind you of anybody else.'
</P>
<P>
   _ Comptroller Carole Keeton Rylander
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
