A1572 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BULLOCK-ACHIEVE19-COX     06-18 0226
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BULLOCK-ACHIEVE19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Bullock's notable accomplishments
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   _ Fought for campaign and election law changes while serving as
secretary of state and pushed for voting rights for 18-year-olds.
</P>
<P>
   _ Headed first consumer protection division at Texas attorney
general's office as an assistant attorney general.
</P>
<P>
   _ Created Texas Performance Review, by which state comptroller
analyzes spending at state agencies and recommends cost-saving
alternatives.
</P>
<P>
   _ As comptroller, was first elected official to enact an equal
opportunity employment program.
</P>
<P>
   _ Was among the first elected officials to use computers in
state government.
</P>
<P>
   _ Helped put all environmental agencies into one department at
the Texas Natural Resource Conservation Commission.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pushed through the 1993 Legislature a constitutional amendment
requiring voters' approval before a state personal income tax could
be enacted.
</P>
<P>
   _ Led efforts to renovate State Cemetery.
</P>
<P>
   _ Worked to revamp state education financing.
</P>
<P>
   _ Ushered through the 1997 Legislature a bill creating the
state's first water conservation management plan.
</P>
<P>
   _ Secured money in the 1998-99 budget for a Texas state museum
in Austin.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
