<HEADLINE>
OLAZABAL PUNCHES HIMSELF OUT OF U.S. OPEN 
</HEADLINE>
  (With GLF-USOPEN) 
(mk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PINEHURST, N.C. _ Jose Maria Olazabal, this year's Masters
champion, withdrew from the U.S. Open on Friday after breaking his
right hand Thursday punching a wall in his hotel room.
</P>
<P>
   Upset after shooting a 75 in the opening round, Olazabal vented
his frustration after returning to his hotel.
</P>
<P>
   Wearing a splint, Olazabal arrived at the Pinehurst No. 2 course
to try a few practice swings. But he soon determined he could not
play, and left the course.
</P>
<P>
   The injury will keep Olazabal from playing for several weeks and
puts his status for the British Open, scheduled for July 15-18, in
doubt.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have a broken bone,'' Olazabal said. ``I hit a wall. It was
my fault.''
</P>
</TEXT>
