<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-MUNSON2-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAJOR_LEAGUE TIME STARTING RIGHT AWAY) 
MUNSON SIGNS WITH TIGERS
</HEADLINE>
 (CORRECTION: REMOVES PARAGRAPH ABOUT(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS BRANAM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ His first swings as a professional baseball player
were in the batting cage at Tiger Stadium, his first paycheck is
the amount of money normally won by a lottery winner, and he gets
to hang out this weekend with his best friend Eric Chavez, who
happens to be the third baseman for the Oakland A's.
</P>
<P>
   The spoils are going to Eric Munson.
</P>
<P>
   Munson, a junior catcher who led USC to a national championship
in 1998, signed with Detroit on Friday, two weeks after the Tigers
made him the No. 3 pick in the major-league draft.
</P>
<P>
   Munson agreed to a four-year major-league contract worth $6.75
million. His signing bonus is $3.5 million and he will get $250,000
this season. He'll earn $750,000 next year, $1 million in 2001 and
$1.25 million in 2002.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't be more excited to be here,'' Munson, 21, told the
Detroit Free Press. ``It's a class organization. . . . I'm kind of
in awe seeing this old stadium. I'm looking forward to seeing
Comerica Park.''
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Moorad, Munson's Newport Beach-based adviser whose clients
include Pat Burrell, last year's No. 1 overall pick, and Arizona
first baseman Travis Lee, negotiated the deal.
</P>
<P>
   Munson will stay in Detroit through Monday, working out with the
Tigers. By coincidence, Oakland's Chavez _ his best friend since
they were 4 years old _ also will be in town those four days with
the Athletics. The two planned to have dinner Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're thrilled that it's worked out that way,'' Munson said.
``We've always dreamed to be on a big-league field, and doing it
together, it's a great time.''
</P>
<P>
   Munson will report to the Tigers' Single-A team in Lakeland,
Fla., next week, then will join West Michigan in the Single-A
Midwest League.
</P>
<P>
   Munson, 21, batted .346 with 15 home runs and 41 RBI this
season. He missed 21 games with a broken right hand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
